sudo -i
Update the hosts file with all nodes
zypepr -n in autoyast
yast2 clone_system
* Note the underscore, not dash
* Output file is /root/autoinst.xml
cp -p autoinst.xml infra6.xml
vi infra6.xml
* Change 105 (the IP of the base node) to 106 for <ipaddr>
* Change <hostname> from infra5 to infra6
** Don't need to change the hosts file entries

scp to deployment host

Deployment host:
cp infra6.xml to /home/admin/autoyast_templates/infra6.xml
* Set up docker
Launch nginx container: docker run --name mynginx  -v /home/admin/autoyast_templates:/usr/share/nginx/html:ro -P -d nginx:latest
Test from infra5: curl http://<ip of deployment host>:<port of nginx>/infra6.xml

Start system from DVD ISO, stop at DVD GRuB screen
* Select "Installation"
* On installation line: `autoyast=http://<ip of deployment host>:<port of nginx>/infra6.xml ifcfg=eth0=<ip of this host>/24,<IP of gateway>,<IP of DNS server,<search domain> hostname=infra6.caaspv4.com
